element.name: Insignificant by Donnacha, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)
element.long-description:
A simple cache localed in a park just off of the town centre in Greystones. Greystones is easily assessable by bus or train with the park a short stroll from the bus stop and train station. Nice area to bring the kids to kick around a ball, with the beach across the road also. If the kids are old enough there's a playground down the road. You'll need to be careful retrieving the cache as the area can be quite busy. Please put the cache back in the location you found it so it won't be easily seen by passers by.
Visit the Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE
element.encoded-hints: Attached to fence behind hedge - 20 paces from end of fence nearest the town. Look for whitish looking bush in front of hedge.
